33:40.685 --> 33:42.353
We came out here
and loved it so much

33:42.387 --> 33:43.855
that we decided
we had to be out here.

33:43.888 --> 33:47.158
And, uh, and dropped it all
and bought a ranch,

33:47.191 --> 33:48.659
and here we are.

33:48.693 --> 33:51.696
The owner of the ranch
just sort of in passing said

33:51.729 --> 33:54.198
that he might be looking
for his next chapter.

33:54.232 --> 33:56.000
You know, we said,
if you're really

33:56.034 --> 33:58.269
ever gonna entertain
the idea of selling this place,

33:58.302 --> 33:59.871
let us know.

33:59.904 --> 34:02.173
And we heard from him
in a week.
<b></b>
Reedus: Oh, really?

34:02.206 --> 34:04.609
So, he kind of called our bluff
rather quickly.

34:04.642 --> 34:06.544
Yeah, but a guy like that
probably was, like,

34:06.577 --> 34:08.413
interviewing you
in his head.
Oh, 100%.

34:08.446 --> 34:10.515
He wouldn't want to leave
this to anyone.

34:10.548 --> 34:11.916
Sometimes
it's just like one thing

34:11.949 --> 34:14.018
that changes the course
of the rest of your life.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.421
And we showed up
in my old Ford pickup,

34:16.454 --> 34:19.357
and it was
almost exactly the same

34:19.390 --> 34:20.925
as his old Ford pickup.

34:20.958 --> 34:23.694
We probably never really
would have had a conversation.

34:23.728 --> 34:25.263
If we picked
a different car

34:25.296 --> 34:26.864
and we showed up
on anything else
or whatever --

34:26.898 --> 34:28.699
And it changed
the course of our lives.

34:28.733 --> 34:30.735
I think if you're open
to see those

34:30.768 --> 34:33.037
and accept them
and move in that direction,

34:33.071 --> 34:34.439
everything works
for the better, you know.

34:34.472 --> 34:35.773
Yep.
<b></b>
That's great.

34:35.807 --> 34:37.542
You just have to be
willing to do it.

34:37.575 --> 34:38.943
Yeah.
<b></b>
That's the hardest part.

34:38.976 --> 34:41.045
So where we going?
<b></b>
We're going to our place.

34:41.079 --> 34:43.081
[Engine starts]

34:43.114 --> 34:46.150
Hey, man, what's the "RR"
on your baseball hat stand for?

34:46.184 --> 34:47.452
Rimrock Ranch.

34:47.485 --> 34:49.720
Ah, I gotta get a hat.
Do you have another one?

34:49.754 --> 34:52.123
I've got one
especially for you.
<b></b>
Yeah.

34:52.156 --> 34:54.058
Barker: [Laughs]
<b></b>
It says ass(bleep)
on the front of it?

34:54.092 --> 34:56.160
[Laughter]

34:56.194 --> 35:04.068
♪♪

35:04.102 --> 35:07.305
Wow, that's super pretty
right there to the right.
<b></b>
Yeah.

35:07.338 --> 35:10.775
All of this.
Holy (bleep)

35:10.808 --> 35:12.910
You guys ever see aliens
out here?

35:12.944 --> 35:15.012
We haven't.
We know some people who have.

35:15.046 --> 35:16.747
But, uh, questionable

35:16.781 --> 35:18.082
what state of mind
they were in.

35:18.116 --> 35:19.317
[Laughter]

35:19.350 --> 35:20.585
I'm keeping
my fingers crossed.

35:20.618 --> 35:21.519
[Laughs]

35:21.552 --> 35:26.591
♪♪

35:26.624 --> 35:29.594
-Oh (bleep)
-What?

35:29.627 --> 35:30.995
Hey, yo,
where'd he go behind me?

35:31.028 --> 35:32.864
Yo,
we lost your boyfriend.

35:32.897 --> 35:37.335
♪♪

35:37.368 --> 35:38.436
[Exhales sharply]

35:38.469 --> 35:39.337
[Sniffs]

35:39.370 --> 35:41.539
All right, come on, girl.

35:41.572 --> 35:44.275
Captain's log,
"Star Trek" Enterprise.

35:44.308 --> 35:45.943
We have run out of gas

35:45.977 --> 35:48.045
in the deserts
of Joshua Tree.

35:48.079 --> 35:51.482
We have one soldier down
back there.

35:51.516 --> 35:53.284
His lovely girlfriend
is here

35:53.317 --> 35:56.187
to keep the fire
burning alive in his honor...

35:56.220 --> 35:57.989
[Laughs]
<b></b>
...in case
he doesn't return.

35:58.022 --> 35:59.290
He's gone.

35:59.323 --> 36:00.625
Never to return.

36:00.658 --> 36:03.394
This looks like
a hostile planet to me.

36:03.427 --> 36:05.963
Although we have met --
<b></b>
I mean, it's not far off.

36:05.997 --> 36:07.231
It is a western.

36:07.265 --> 36:08.666
Yeah, we have met --

36:08.699 --> 36:10.701
we have met locals
that seem very nice,

36:10.735 --> 36:12.336
but there is
sort of a weird

36:12.370 --> 36:14.505
desert twinkle
in their eye.

36:14.539 --> 36:17.141
So they might have kept him
and turned him into chili.

36:17.175 --> 36:18.843
We don't know.

36:19.210 --> 36:24.515
[Engine revs]

36:24.549 --> 36:26.350
Thank God
you're not chili right now.

36:26.384 --> 36:27.652
I'll explain later.

36:27.685 --> 36:28.686
[Laughter]

36:28.719 --> 36:29.854
Thanks for waiting.

36:29.887 --> 36:32.056
Of course.
<b></b>
I appreciate it.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.992
It's rude
to watch your girl

36:35.026 --> 36:37.662
ride off with Norman Reedus
into the sunset.

36:37.695 --> 36:40.164
[Laughter]

36:40.198 --> 36:42.166
Stranded on a ride.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.068
Season 2.

36:44.101 --> 36:46.904
♪♪

36:52.476 --> 36:56.681
♪♪

36:56.714 --> 37:01.485
♪♪

37:01.519 --> 37:02.920
Well,
welcome to Rimrock Ranch.

37:02.954 --> 37:05.489
This is awesome up here.
This is so cool.
<b></b>
[Laughs]

37:05.523 --> 37:08.659
Reedus: The Rimrock Ranch.

37:08.693 --> 37:10.027
It's an end for travelers,

37:10.061 --> 37:11.495
a place for friends to gather,

37:11.529 --> 37:14.232
a place to say "I do."

37:14.265 --> 37:16.667
A place you could
tune up and rock out.

37:16.701 --> 37:19.937
It's a place Gwen and Eric
call home.

37:19.971 --> 37:22.173
-Hi, Eric.
-Hi!

37:22.206 --> 37:24.375
Woman: [Laughs]

37:24.408 --> 37:26.210
What's up?
Hi, I'm Norman.

37:26.244 --> 37:28.212
Hi. Annie.
<b></b>
Nice to meet you.

37:28.246 --> 37:29.547
What's your name?
Lisa.

37:29.580 --> 37:31.449
You're adorable.
Norman. Nice to meet you.

37:31.482 --> 37:34.552
Barker: She's a badass
biker chick already.
<b></b>
Lisa: Hi!

37:34.585 --> 37:36.220
Such a good vibe up here,
all these people.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.888
Yeah, isn't it?
<b></b>
This is super-cool.

37:37.922 --> 37:38.889
It's our desert family.

37:38.923 --> 37:42.560
♪♪

37:42.593 --> 37:44.729
Who's this little dude?
<b></b>
This is Ellie May.

37:44.762 --> 37:45.896
Hi, Ellie May.

37:45.930 --> 37:47.198
She's my little princess.

37:47.231 --> 37:48.733
Oh, my God.
Hi, cutie pie.

37:48.766 --> 37:50.534
Is this your truck?
<b></b>
This is Jim's truck.

37:50.568 --> 37:54.071
So, um, I have a '67,
This is a '69.

37:54.105 --> 37:55.640
I used to have
a Ford F-150.

37:55.673 --> 37:57.575
Dean: Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

37:57.608 --> 38:00.411
Well...
<b></b>
I had to stop for gas
at every gas station.

38:00.444 --> 38:03.080
...Speaking of Fords.

38:03.114 --> 38:05.216
Dude. This is bananas.

38:05.249 --> 38:06.284
Yeah.

38:06.317 --> 38:08.286
Tell me the story with this.

38:08.319 --> 38:10.454
Um, so,
it's a Ford GT40,

38:10.488 --> 38:12.757
replica of
the original car.

38:12.790 --> 38:15.760
I built it, spent about
three years of my life.

38:15.793 --> 38:17.795
It's my favorite car
of all time,

38:17.828 --> 38:20.298
and no one can afford
the real ones, so.

38:20.331 --> 38:21.732
You're a badass.

38:21.766 --> 38:23.801
I couldn't even make this
as a little model.

38:23.834 --> 38:24.602
[Laughs]

38:24.635 --> 38:29.106
[Engine starts, revs]

38:29.140 --> 38:32.176
♪♪

38:32.209 --> 38:33.311
And away we go.

38:33.344 --> 38:35.246
This is crazy.

38:35.279 --> 38:36.781
You can feel the power.

38:36.814 --> 38:39.950
440 horsepower
in a 2,300 pound car,

38:39.984 --> 38:41.986
so that's like
the equivalent of

38:42.019 --> 38:44.588
you know, a power-to-weight
ratio of a modern NASCAR.

38:44.622 --> 38:46.924
Got a bunch of weirdos
out here.

38:46.957 --> 38:48.426
Welcome to the desert.

38:56.233 --> 39:06.210
♪♪

39:06.243 --> 39:08.646
♪♪

39:08.679 --> 39:10.548
Tell me if you want me
to slow down.

39:10.581 --> 39:12.817
Oh, you're all right
as long as you feel good.

39:12.850 --> 39:14.185
I feel good.

39:14.218 --> 39:15.986
I feel real good!

39:16.020 --> 39:25.996
♪♪

39:26.030 --> 39:35.806
♪♪

39:35.840 --> 39:39.210
Reedus: For me, riding
is a visceral experience.

39:39.243 --> 39:41.178
Man and machine become one.

39:41.212 --> 39:43.581
Two men and a machine?

39:43.614 --> 39:47.017
That's a threesome
I can get behind.

39:47.051 --> 39:50.187
I feel like my penis just got
like five inches longer.

39:50.221 --> 39:52.156
[Laughs]

39:52.189 --> 39:54.325
♪♪

39:54.358 --> 39:56.026
I'm not adjusting
your seatbelt.

39:56.060 --> 39:57.728
[Laughs]

40:00.731 --> 40:04.168
Dude, that was amazing.
<b></b>
[Laughs]

40:04.201 --> 40:06.103
I'm glad you enjoyed it.

40:06.137 --> 40:08.372
Seriously, you're gonna have
to leave your girlfriend

40:08.406 --> 40:11.041
because I'm about
to propose to you.

40:11.075 --> 40:12.510
[Laughs]

40:12.543 --> 40:14.245
Unreal.
I accept.

40:14.278 --> 40:17.948
♪♪

40:17.982 --> 40:20.518
As the sun goes down
behind the desert hills,

40:20.551 --> 40:22.753
casting silhouettes
in its absence,

40:22.787 --> 40:25.122
signaling the end of the day.

40:25.156 --> 40:27.124
Right here, right now,

40:27.158 --> 40:30.528
the L.A. local band The Shrine
gets the party started.

40:30.561 --> 40:40.538
[The Shrine's
"I Can't Control It" plays]

40:40.571 --> 40:46.877
♪♪

40:46.911 --> 40:50.247
♪ I'm sick, I must confess ♪

40:50.281 --> 40:53.584
♪ Without your love,
I am a mess ♪

40:53.617 --> 40:56.754
♪ I do bad things to myself ♪

40:56.787 --> 40:59.757
♪ Without your love,
without your help ♪

40:59.790 --> 41:01.792
♪ I can't control it ♪

41:03.027 --> 41:05.796
♪ I can't control it, baby ♪

41:06.464 --> 41:09.667
♪ I'm lookin' in the eyes
of the beast, my friend ♪

41:09.700 --> 41:11.702
♪ I can't control it ♪

41:13.871 --> 41:19.977
♪♪

41:21.111 --> 41:22.913
Reedus:
We all hold onto those things

41:22.947 --> 41:25.416
that bridge the gap
between our past and our future.

41:25.449 --> 41:27.685
Hanging photographs
on the wall,

41:27.718 --> 41:29.453
collecting old parts,

41:29.487 --> 41:32.456
preserving time,
preserving our loved ones,

41:32.490 --> 41:33.757
keepsakes that offer comfort

41:33.791 --> 41:36.427
in times
when we lose our bearings.

41:36.460 --> 41:39.864
They remind us of who we are
and how far we've come.

41:39.897 --> 41:42.867
Throughout our lives,
we collect these memories.

41:42.900 --> 41:45.302
And when you piece them
all together,

41:45.336 --> 41:47.471
they reveal our journey.

41:47.505 --> 41:49.807
Whoa.

41:49.840 --> 41:51.375
I gotta thank you guys
for having me, man.

41:51.408 --> 41:52.676
Thank you.

41:52.710 --> 41:54.211
Oh, thanks for coming.
<b></b>
This is such a --

41:54.245 --> 41:56.614
such a good life up here,
you know what I mean?

41:56.647 --> 41:57.815
We think so.

41:57.848 --> 42:00.050
Dean: The best thing
about living here

42:00.084 --> 42:01.986
are all these people
right here.
Yep.
Aw.

42:02.019 --> 42:05.189
This is like, um,
the greatest sense of community

42:05.222 --> 42:07.491
I've ever experienced
living anywhere in my life.

42:07.525 --> 42:09.560
Yeah, I'm coming back,
for sure, yeah.

42:09.593 --> 42:11.028
We have a gift for you.

42:11.061 --> 42:12.463
Yeah, I wanted
to give you something.
<b></b>
Shut up.

42:12.496 --> 42:14.298
A little, uh, something

42:14.331 --> 42:16.333
you can remember
this place by.
<b></b>
No way.

42:16.367 --> 42:19.069
No way.
And, um...

42:19.103 --> 42:21.005
This black hat is, um,

42:21.038 --> 42:22.506
something you have to earn,
so --

42:22.540 --> 42:24.041
[Laughter]

42:24.074 --> 42:25.976
-You get of one each.
-We'll talk about that later.

42:26.010 --> 42:27.011
[Laughter]

42:27.044 --> 42:29.380
Does this have anything
to do with the proposal?

42:29.413 --> 42:30.881
[Laughter]
<b></b>
Is this
honeymoon material?

42:30.915 --> 42:32.416
Is that what
you're talking about?

42:32.449 --> 42:34.919
Yo -- Give me a hug, dude.
Yeah, you're awesome, man.

42:34.952 --> 42:36.820
You are, too.
<b></b>
Thank you for everything.

42:36.854 --> 42:37.855
Yeah.

42:37.888 --> 42:40.991
Reedus: The Rimrock Ranch hat
isn't just a hat.

42:41.025 --> 42:43.928
It's a reminder of my time
here in Joshua Tree

42:43.961 --> 42:45.829
and the friendships
I've made in the desert,

42:45.863 --> 42:48.432
and the ones
I've maintained in the city,

42:48.465 --> 42:50.668
and the ride
it took to get here.

42:50.701 --> 42:52.603
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

42:52.636 --> 42:55.005
Reedus:
No, this isn't just a hat.

42:55.039 --> 42:58.008
It's a reminder of a ride
that I'm never gonna forget.

42:58.809 --> 43:00.344
Man #1:
The engagement is on.

43:00.377 --> 43:02.212
[Laughter]
<b></b>
Man #2: Yeah.

43:02.246 --> 43:06.150
♪♪
